t inside the United States. When Thais arrived in Los Angeles, they reinvented and repackaged Thai food in various ways to meet the rising popularity of the cuisine in urban and suburban spaces. Padoongpatt opens up the history and politics of Thai food for the first time, all while demonstrating how race emerges in seemingly mundane and unexpected places.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aCooking, Thai. 0aThaiszCaliforniazLos AngelesxSocial conditions. 0aThaiszCaliforniazLos AngelesxSocial life and customs. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh  a1980s.  aamerica.  aarchival.  aasian cuisine.  aasian food.  acalifornia.  acold war.  acommunity.  acooking.  aculinary scene.  aculinary.  acultural history.  aculture.  aeating.  aeconomy.  aethnic groups.  aethnic.  afood and drink.  afood culture.  afood history.  afoodways.  aimmigrant.  alos angeles.  aspices.  asuburban.  athai american.  athai cuisine.  athai culture.  athai food.  athai identity.  athailand.  aurban.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029373140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966925423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520966925/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY